race.comment: MANAAL (2) dynamic mare who's gone to a new level this campaign. Shouldered the 58kg when a tenacious winner of the G2 Golden Pendant at Rosehill. Berry sticks from the right draw and hard to see some of these turning the tables. MISS ROUMBINI (3) comes up from Victoria after rocketing late from near last on the turn when an unlucky second over 1400m in the G1 Sir Rupert Clarke Stakes at Caulfield. Back in class and maps to get a better run. Leading prospect. FIRESTORM (4) ready to peak third-up but will be giving some of these a big start. Took good ground off MANAAL first-up before jumping in grade when ninth in the Alan Brown Stakes at Rosehill over this distance. Will be hoping they overdo it up front. STEFI MAGNETICA (1) normally takes a few runs before she hits her top. Failed to make any real impression when fourth in the G2 Sheraco over 1200m at Rosehill on September 13. Kept fresh and like the way she closed off in her recent 1030m trial. Respect. OH DIAMOND LIL (6) next best.
